      <Content>The phrases δίδωμι κλήρους in {S:04400102600006} and βάλλω κλήρους in {S:04202303400038} (βάλλω κλῆρον in {S:04002703500018}) refer to choosing someone by means of casting lots, but these expressions may be interpreted in a strictly literal sense and thus are not treated here as idioms (see {D:6.219}).</Content>
